Hi there.
I do LightGBM simplifications for my own purpose.
The restrictions are:
-Single threaded. No network no OMP parallel
-Features are all numeric without missing values (so Dataset is dense)
-only binary and regression objectives
-only single class label
-optimized for prediction on streaming data (after training)

The main question is: So if there are no missing values in features then can i completly remove
`default_bin` and `BinMapper::GetDefaultBin()` from code?

The Lines that bother me:
1)`Dataset::FixHistogram`  `if (default_bin > 0)`
2)`FeatureGroup` constructors `if (bin_mappers_[i]->GetDefaultBin() == 0) {
        num_bin -= 1;
      }`
3)`FeatureGroup::PushData`  `if (bin == bin_mappers_[sub_feature_idx]->GetDefaultBin()) { return; }` and `if (bin_mappers_[sub_feature_idx]->GetDefaultBin() == 0) {
      bin -= 1;
    }`
4)`DenseBinIterator` constructor `if (default_bin_ == 0) {
      bias_ = 1;
    } else {
      bias_ = 0;
    }`
5)`DenseBin::Split` `if (default_bin == 0) {
      th -= 1;
      t_default_bin -= 1;
    }`  and `if ((default_left && missing_type == MissingType::Zero) || (default_bin <= threshold && missing_type != MissingType::Zero)) {
        default_indices = lte_indices;
        default_count = &lte_count;
      }`
6)`HistogramPool::DynamicChangeSize`  `if (train_data->FeatureBinMapper(i)->GetDefaultBin() == 0) {
          feature_metas_[i].bias = 1;
        } else {
          feature_metas_[i].bias = 0;
        }`  and  `if (train_data->FeatureBinMapper(j)->GetDefaultBin() == 0) {
          num_bin -= 1;
        }`
and so on


Can you also suggest any other simplifications that i can made according to restictions above?

